Package: mpca
Title: Multilevel PCA for Composite Indices with Measurement Error Correction
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("MPCA", "Authors", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "mpca@example.com")
Description: Implements measurement-error-corrected principal component
    analysis (MPCA) for composite indices where each sub-index has
    associated uncertainty estimates from bootstrapped confidence intervals.
    The package provides: (1) a three-pass missing-data imputation
    hierarchy (within-group linear interpolation, time-period-mean fallback,
    global-mean fallback); (2) an Option Filter minimum-coverage filter;
    (3) naive PC1 aggregation; (4) attenuation correction via
    disattenuation of correlations (Spearman 1904), with nearest
    positive-semidefinite projection; (5) a two-stage bootstrap that
    propagates both Stage-1 measurement error and Stage-2 sampling
    uncertainty into composite confidence intervals; and (6) standard
    post-processing (z-score, Box-Cox, min-max rescaling).
